  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "In a medium saucepan, combine quinoa and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 12 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.",
    "Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, warm olive oil. Add onions and garlic, sautéing for about 3-4 minutes or until soft.",
    "Add red bell pepper and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Stir in ground cumin, smoked paprika, cinnamon powder, and salt. Cook for another minute.",
    "Transfer cooked quinoa to the skillet with vegetables. Toss well to coat evenly.",
    "Bake in preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the quinoa is crispy on top and golden brown.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving."
  ],
